model_specification:
U = beta_bias + beta_fair * (split_self - (token_self/(token_self + token_opp)) * combined_earning)
p_accept = 1/(1 + exp(-U))
accept ~ Bernoulli(p_accept)
model_summary: A model in which the utility of accepting a proposal is computed as a linear function of the deviation between the offered share (split_self) and the fair share based on pretask tokens. Two learnable parameters – a bias (beta_bias) and a fairness sensitivity (beta_fair) – determine how this deviation influences utility. The utility is then transformed via a logistic function to yield the probability of acceptance.
